Spanish Stocks: Banco Santander, Bankinter, Inditex Move

-- B y   A l e x i s   X y d i a s
-- 
2011-03-08T10:28:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/spanish-stocks-banco-santander-bankinter-inditex-move.html
Spain’s  IBEX 35 index (IBEX)  dropped 21.8,
or 0.2 percent, to 10,473.9 at 11:21 a.m. in Madrid. The Madrid
Stock Exchange General Index lost 0.3 percent.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.    Banco Santander SA (SAN)   dropped 7.3 cents, or 0.9
percent, to 8.17 euros, falling for a seventh day. Spain’s
biggest lender was cut to “neutral” from “overweight” at
HSBC Holdings Plc.  Separately,  La Caixa  and Santander closed the accounts of
Iran’s embassy in Madrid to comply with financial sanctions
against the country over its nuclear program, Press TV reported,
without citing anyone.    Bankinter SA (BKT)   fell 1.8 cents, or 0.4 percent, to
4.47 euros, its seventh straight retreat. The Spanish bank may
announce today the sale of 400 million euros ($559 million) in
convertible bonds to meet  capital requirements , Expansion
reported, without citing anyone.    Inditex SA (ITX)  , the retailer that runs the Zara
clothing stores, fell 1.7 percent to 52.39 euros. Cotton rose to
a record in New York yesterday on signs that global supplies may
not satisfy demand in China, the world’s biggest consumer and
producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexis Xydias in London at 
 axydias@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  